  "texts": [
    "70), with edge reinforcement ρ ranging from 0.1 to 10.",
    "Similarly to the UMT, we perform 100 simulations for each set of parameters, and report the results in Fig. 2b, c.",
    "For both UMST and ERRW, we find that the values of β 2 do not differ much from their corresponding value of β 1 -as shown by the great proximity of the points (β 1, β 2) to the bisector.",
    "This means that also these models fail to reproduce the empirical variability of higher-order Heaps' exponents with respect to the 1st-order one.",
    "Moreover, we notice in (b) that for the UMST we only obtain exponents with either very low (up to 0.4) or very high (close to 1) values."
